#- I have compiled this guide through my travels with the purpose of providing intelligence for the standing elected council. This guide provides information about various cities, including possible exploits and weaknesses, along with recommendations.
#- SECRET - NOT FOR PUBLIC VIEWING

Exposure of this document could strain the relationships with cities or persons named.
#- Neverwhere

Mostly inactive town, one player is on occasionally.
Massive artistic buildings reinforced with stone. Easy to break into, chests are unlocked and contain numerous building supplies. No reddit presence. (-,+)
#- Commonwealth

Massive rail hub. Access can be given to the entrance into the town, which includes a number of snitches in the area. Stone reinforced obsidian around the rail area, vulnerable town otherwise. Massive shopping area. (-,+)
#- Commonwealth Cnt.

Snitches include the rail system leading in and out of CW. This can be used to track movement of potential targets. Background check required to get permission, consists of reddit search of your name. Active on Reddit.
#- Mount Augusta

20min ride from Viridian. Low population, large city - snitch density unknown. Uneducated/young populace. Can be manipulated easily. (I was offered a "loan" of a D silk touch pick for 10%) (+,+)
#- New Detroit

Direct neighbors with MA. Leader Screenname is in charge of several towns on the map. We have an insider, Tvmats who is working to take control of the empire. Will work in our favor if requested. (+,+)
#- Vinland

Small mining town in the south. Good place to hide persecuted members if necessary. Iron is plentiful in this region once you take the train to South Vinland. (-,+)
#- Nexus/Vail

Stone-reinf. glowstone all over. Empty when I visited. Large building filled with redstone - grinder? Unchecked griefing. Massive vine farms, snitches unknown. No shops.
Fairly heavy rail hub.
(-,0)
#- Fellowship

Most active town. Huge reddit citizenry. Large city, major rail and economic hub. Possibly the "capital" of reddit on the server, alongside Orion. Massive shopping mall. Everything you need can be bought here.
(+,-)
#- Recommendations
(Security)
*Provide passports for citizens, and equip select members with censuses to keep out spies/griefers
*Install snitches throughout the town
*Provide emergency arms for the citizens in the event of an attack
#- Recommendations
(Economic)
~Participate in international commerce with Commonwealth and other towns.
~Raid and take advantage of other towns' exploits.
~Keep /int/IS's location hidden.
#- Recommendations
(Sustainability)
-Create a town vault
-Establish a northern outpost (currently no chan presence in the upper hemisphere)
-Plant members in potential high-value towns for recon and manipulation.
#- Version 1

Updated guides will come as I explore more.
#- 